Chapter 0 - Introduction

In 2006, Feoffrey Hinton et al published a paper showing dnn recognizaing handwritten digits w/ state-of-art precision (>98%).

Python frameworks:
1. Sikit-learn (https://scikit-learn.org) created in 2007
2. Tensorflow (https://tensorflow.org) created at Google and was open sourced in November 2015, and version 2 released in 2019.
3. Keras (https://keras.io) is a high-level deep learning API. Keras comes with TensoFlow, and it relies on TensorFlow for all the intensive computations.

Book code example: https://github.com/ageron/handson-ml3

Prerequisites:
-> python: (https://learnpython.org/ --- https://docs.python.org/3/tutorial/)
-> Numpy (https://humpy.org)
-> Pandas (https://pandas.pydata.org)
-> Matplotlib (https://matplotlib.org)
-> linear algebra
-> differential calculus
-> other mathematical concepts
online tutorial on colab: https://colab.research.google.com/github/ageron/handson-ml3/blob/main/index.ipynb
online maths help: https://www.khanacademy.org/

